- Summary/description: Taken from @ApiOperation: value ("Returns a document") and notes ("This method allows employees to get a document by a given id.").
- Path parameter: id is a long (primitive long) extracted with @PathVariable; therefore modeled as integer with format int64, required and in "path".
- Security: Method is annotated with @Secured("ROLE_EMPLOYEE"); I represent this as a security requirement on the operation referencing a scheme name ROLE_EMPLOYEE (as an operation-level requirement). Note: the security scheme definition itself is not included here (per instructions).
- Responses observed in code:
  - 200 OK: returns a FileSystemResource serving the physical file with Content-Type "application/pdf", body is a PDF binary. Response also sets headers "Content-Disposition" and "Cache-Control". These headers are documented under the 200 response.
  - 404 Not Found: code returns a ResponseEntity with headers and status NOT_FOUND, sets Content-Type to application/json but no body is present. Represented with application/json content and an empty object schema.
  - 401 Unauthorized: code returns ResponseEntity with status UNAUTHORIZED and Content-Type application/json, no body. Represented similarly to 404.
- I did not add fields or components not present in the code (no global securitySchemes, no example responses, etc.). The Operation object below includes only fields derived from the controller implementation.

